<h2 style="text-align: left;">Screen Printing: What You Need to Know</h2>
Screen printing is a popular way to market your business or personalize gifts for clients and friends. We offer standard screen printing, digital printing, and CMYK in any sized production run. We do not use water based inks, and our colors are Pantone coated.

[typography font="Cantarell" size="28" size_format="px"]Ordering information:[/typography]<br />

<ol>
<li> You need to send your chosen design via <a title="Screenprinting Submit" href="http://www.acshomeandwork.com/screenprinting/">email</a> in a PDF file. Vectored art files are preferable. JPEG files are acceptable for putting together ideas for your design, but PDF is required for formatting and printing.</li>

<li>There is a $50/hour charge for any design that has to be redrawn or reformatted.</li>

<li>If you have a certain color you want, please provide the Pantone color number, or request it to be matched.</li>

<li>Each new design submitted will have a <em>one time art set</em>¬†up fee of $50 for standard screen printing, or $25 for digital printing.</li>

<li>Screen changes are $20 per color (a <em>one time charge</em>, as screens rarely need to be replaced), and a $6 wash screen charge, for color changes on the same screen. Digital printing does not use screens, so there are no charges.</li>

<li>We will screen print on all of our <a title="Flour Sack Towels" href="http://www.acshomeandwork.com/shop/test-page/">flour sack towels</a>,<a title="kitchen towels" href="http://www.acshomeandwork.com/c/kitchen-linens/kitchen-towels/"> kitchen towels</a>, <a title="kitchen napkins" href="http://www.acshomeandwork.com/c/kitchen-linens/kitchen-napkins/">napkins </a>and <a title="aprons" href="http://www.acshomeandwork.com/c/kitchen-linens/aprons/">aprons</a>. We do not recommend screen printing for our terry products.</li>

<li>We will email you a mockup/proof that you must approve before your order goes to print, and will work with you to make sure we have placement, size and color correct before printing.</li>

<li>Lead time is usually two weeks from proof approval to production, but <strong>please check current conditions</strong>, as the schedule can fill up pretty quickly.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Pricing for standard screen printing in one color only (on light fabrics):</h3>
<ul>
<li>100 items: $1.80</li>
<li>500 items: $1.50</li>
<li>1000+ items: $1.10</li>
</ul>
<h3>Pricing for the screen printing in two colors:</h3>
<ul>
<li>100 items: $1.90</li>
<li>500 items: $1.60</li>
<li>1000 items: $1.20</li>
</ul>

<p align="justify">Pricing for more than two colors is an additional 10 cents per towel, per each color added, and pricing for orders under 50 qty will incur a minimum order charge of $20.00.</p>

